author: @goldenbananas1389
text: if anyone wants to know how to test it on a new image. first have it save your model to a file then i used a seperate python script to and did this: Image_size = (your image size) CatDogModel = tf.keras.models.load_model('put the name of your model save file here') ImagePath = "(Path to your image)" Image = cv2.imread(ImagePath, cv2.IMREAD_GRAYSCALE) NewImage = cv2.resize(Image, (Image_size, Image_size)) NewImage = np.array(NewImage).reshape(-1, Image_size, Image_size, 1)  prediction = CatDogModel.predict([NewImage]) a = prediction[0] print(a)  0 is dog and 1 is cat.  I dont know if I did it in the best way but that's what I did and it works.
